  "commit_message": "fix(oidc): accept string repository_id/owner_id claims from GitHub\n\nGitHub Actions OIDC tokens ship every numeric identifier as a JSON\n*string* — ``\"repository_id\": \"74\"``, ``\"repository_owner_id\": \"65\"``,\n``\"actor_id\": \"12\"`` — per the example-subject-claims table in\nGitHub's OIDC hardening docs.\n\nThe service-layer validator gated the binding lookup behind\n``isinstance(..., int)``, which is False for every real-world token.\nPyJWT verified signature/issuer/audience/expiry just fine; the\nexchange",
